# Testing Strategy\n90: \n91: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## References\n96: \n97: - [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime)\n98: - [AR-003: client-go Generated Code](../AR-003/)\n99: - [AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework](../AR-004/)\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Design: K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ©\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Large  \n\nThe K8s Reconciler Controller provides event-driven reconciliation for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the AgentCube system. It uses controller-runtime to watch resources, manage lifecycle transitions, and ensure cluster state matches desired state.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé                     Kubernetes API Server                                   Ōöé","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775852050543,"end":1775852050584}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852050587,"sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","part":{"id":"prt_d7907d00f001w2m298JYQj840k","messageID":"msg_d7907bbef001ym8fBprbO0me51","sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Task Breakdown\n2: \n3: ## T001: Controller Manager Setup\n4: **Status:** Open  \n5: **Assignee:** TBD  \n6: **Estimated Hours:** 4\n7: \n8: - Initialize controller-runtime manager\n9: - Configure scheme with CRD types\n10: - Set up health probes and metrics\n11: - Add graceful shutdown handling\n12: \n13: ## T002: Resource Watchers\n14: **Status:** Open  \n15: **Assignee:** TBD  \n16: **Estimated Hours:** 6\n17: \n18: - Implement AgentRuntime watcher\n19: - Implement CodeInterpreter watcher\n20: - Configure event predicates\n21: - Filter irrelevant events\n22: \n23: ## T003: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n24: **Status:** Open  \n25: **Assignee:** TBD  \n26: **Estimated Hours:** 8\n27: \n28: - Implement reconcile loop\n29: - Add finalizer management\n30: - Handle create/update/delete events\n31: - Update status conditions\n32: \n33: ## T004: CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n34: **Status:** Open  \n35: **Assignee:** TBD  \n36: **Estimated Hours:** 8\n37: \n38: - Implement reconcile loop\n39: - Add finalizer management\n40: - Handle create/update/delete events\n41: - Update status conditions\n42: \n43: ## T005: Error Handling & Backoff\n44: **Status:** Open  \n45: **Assignee:** TBD  \n46: **Estimated Hours:** 4\n47: \n48: - Implement exponential backoff\n49: - Configure retry policies\n50: - Classify error types\n51: - Add error metrics\n52: \n53: ## T006: Metrics & Observability\n54: **Status:** Open  \n55: **Assignee:** TBD  \n56: **Estimated Hours:** 4\n57: \n58: - Add reconciliation metrics\n59: - Configure structured logging\n60: - Implement tracing hooks\n61: - Document observability\n62: \n63: ## T007: Service Layer Integration\n64: **Status:** Open  \n65: **Assignee:** TBD  \n66: **Estimated Hours:** 6\n67: \n68: - Integrate with WorkloadManager\n69: - Connect to AR-005/AR-006 handlers\n70: - Verify event propagation\n71: - Add integration tests\n72: \n73: ## T008: Unit Tests\n74: **Status:** Open  \n75: **Assignee:** TBD  \n76: **Estimated Hours:** 6\n77: \n78: - Test reconciler logic\n79: - Test finalizer handling\n80: - Test error scenarios\n81: - Achieve coverage goals\n82: \n83: ## T009: Integration Tests\n84: **Status:** Open  \n85: **Assignee:** TBD  \n86: **Estimated Hours:** 6\n87: \n88: - E2E tests with fake client\n89: - Kind cluster deployment tests\n90: - Verify metrics collection\n91: - Test concurrent reconciliations\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Summary\n96: \n97: - **Total Tasks:** 9\n98: - **Total Estimated Hours:** 52\n99: - **Status:** Not Started\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Task Breakdown\n\n## T001: Controller Manager Setup\n**Status:** Open  \n**Assignee:** TBD  \n**Estimated Hours:** 4\n\n- Initialize controller-runtime manager\n- Configure scheme with CRD types\n- Set up health probes and metrics\n- Add graceful shutdown handling\n\n## T002: Resource Watchers\n**Status:** Open  \n**Assignee:** TBD  \n**Estimated Hours:** 6\n\n- Implement AgentRuntime watcher\n- Implement CodeInterpreter watcher\n- Configure event predicates","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775852050549,"end":1775852050586}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852050591,"sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","part":{"id":"prt_d7907cbdc0010tcXbSGb5zJbpQ","messageID":"msg_d7907bbef001ym8fBprbO0me51","sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ©\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-007  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** L  \n9: \n10: Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes configuration and WorkloadManager configuration\n22: - **WHEN** the operator calls `controllerManager.Start(ctx)`\n23: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n24:   1. Create a new controller-runtime manager with the provided configuration\n25:   2. Register the AgentRuntimeReconciler with the manager\n26:   3. Register the CodeInterpreterReconciler with the manager\n27:   4. Start all controllers in separate goroutines\n28:   5. Block until context cancellation or error\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses in-cluster config\n31: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n32: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL use `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to get in-cluster configuration\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses kubeconfig\n36: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n37: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Controller manager shuts down gracefully\n41: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running with active reconciliations\n42: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n44:   1. Stop accepting new reconciliation requests\n45:   2. Wait for in-progress reconciliations to complete (up to graceful timeout)\n46:   3. Stop all watches and release resources\n47:   4. Return without error\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Controller manager health check\n50: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running\n51: - **WHEN** the `/readyz` endpoint is called\n52: - **THEN** it SHALL return ready only when all controllers are started and caches are synced\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n57: \n58: The system SHALL implement a reconciler for AgentRuntime resources.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Reconcile new AgentRuntime creation\n61: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `new-runtime` is created in namespace `default`\n62: - **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n64:   1. Fetch the AgentRuntime object from the API server\n65:   2. Set initial status phase to `Pending`\n66:   3. Add finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n67:   4. Create the underlying sandbox Pod\n68:   5. Set OwnerReference on the Pod pointing to the AgentRuntime\n69:   6. Update status with `SandboxCreated` condition set to `True`\n70:   7. Requeue after 5 seconds to check sandbox status\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox running\n73: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Running` phase\n74: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n75: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n76:   1. Check the Pod status via API server\n77:   2. Update AgentRuntime status phase to `Running`\n78:   3. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n79:   4. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n80:   5. Update `Status.PodIP` with the pod's IP address\n81:   6. Update `Status.SandboxID` with the pod's UID\n82:   7. Update `Status.StartTime` with the pod's start time\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox failure\n85: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Failed` phase\n86: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n88:   1. Update status phase to `Failed`\n89:   2. Set `Failed` condition to `True` with reason and message\n90:   3. Set `Ready` condition to `False`\n91:   4. Record the failure reason in `Status.Reason`\n92:   5. Record error message in `Status.Message`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime spec update\n95: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with generation `2` and observedGeneration `1`\n96: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Detect the spec change (generation != observedGeneration)\n99:   2. Set phase to `Pending` during update\n100:   3. Apply the new spec to the sandbox resources\n101:   4. Update `Status.ObservedGeneration` to match generation\n102:   5. Requeue to monitor the update progress\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime with finalizer on deletion\n105: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp set and finalizer present\n106: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n108:   1. Set phase to `Pending` (terminating state)\n109:   2. Delete the associated sandbox Pod\n110:   3. Delete any associated Services or Ingress resources\n111:   4. Remove the finalizer from the AgentRuntime\n112:   5. Allow Kubernetes to garbage collect the AgentRuntime\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Handle AgentRuntime not found\n115: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for an AgentRuntime that no longer exists\n116: - **WHEN** the reconciler fetches the resource\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL return without error (object was deleted)\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n122: \n123: The system SHALL implement a reconciler for CodeInterpreter resources.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Reconcile new CodeInterpreter creation\n126: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `new-interpreter` is created in namespace `default`\n127: - **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n129:   1. Fetch the CodeInterpreter object from the API server\n130:   2. Set initial `Ready` status to `false`\n131:   3. Add finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n132:   4. Create the sandbox Pod from `spec.template`\n133:   5. Configure ports from `spec.ports`\n134:   6. Set OwnerReference on created resources\n135:   7. Add `SandboxCreated` condition with status `True`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter with warm pool\n138: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.warmPoolSize > 0`\n139: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n141:   1. Create a SandboxClaim instead of direct Sandbox\n142:   2. Set `SandboxClaimCreated` condition\n143:   3. Monitor the SandboxClaim status\n144:   4. Update CodeInterpreter status when sandbox is assigned\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter ready state\n147: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a running sandbox Pod\n148: - **WHEN** the pod passes readiness checks\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n150:   1. Set `Status.Ready` to `true`\n151:   2. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n152:   3. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n153:   4. Record the ready transition timestamp\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter auth configuration\n156: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.authMode=picod`\n157: - **WHEN** the reconciler creates the sandbox\n158: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n159:   1. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n160:   2. Configure authentication sidecar if required\n161:   3. Set appropriate labels for auth routing\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter deletion\n164: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with deletion timestamp set\n165: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n166: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n167:   1. Release warm pool sandboxes if applicable\n168:   2. Delete the SandboxClaim or Sandbox\n169:   3. Clean up associated resources\n170:   4. Remove the finalizer\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: Event-Driven Watch and Reconciliation\n175: \n176: The system SHALL use informers to watch for resource changes and trigger reconciliation.\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime events\n179: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime reconciler is running\n180: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, or deleted\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n182:   1. Receive the event from the API server watch stream\n183:   2. Map the event to a reconciliation request\n184:   3. Add the request to the work queue\n185:   4. Wake up a worker to process the request\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n188: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter reconciler is running\n189: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter resource changes\n190: - **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation request for that resource\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Watch owned Pod events\n193: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has created a sandbox Pod\n194: - **WHEN** the Pod status changes (e.g., transitions to Running)\n195: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n196:   1. Map the Pod event to its owning AgentRuntime\n197:   2. Enqueue a reconciliation request for the AgentRuntime\n198:   3. Trigger status update based on Pod state\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Watch owned Service events\n201: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter has created a Service\n202: - **WHEN** the Service endpoints are updated\n203: - **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation for the owning CodeInterpreter\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Handle watch reconnection\n206: - **GIVEN** the API server watch connection is lost\n207: - **WHEN** the connection drops\n208: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n209:   1. Log the disconnection event\n210:   2. Attempt to reconnect with exponential backoff\n211:   3. Resync the cache on reconnection\n212:   4. Continue processing without data loss\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### Requirement: Reconcile Queue with Rate Limiting\n217: \n218: The system SHALL implement a work queue with rate limiting for reconciliation requests.\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Add request to queue\n221: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime`\n222: - **WHEN** the request is enqueued\n223: - **THEN** the system SHALL add it to the work queue with the resource namespace and name\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Process request from queue\n226: - **GIVEN** a worker is available and a request is in the queue\n227: - **WHEN** the worker dequeues the request\n228: - **THEN** it SHALL call the appropriate reconciler's `Reconcile()` method\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Rate limit failed reconciliations\n231: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a retryable error\n232: - **WHEN** the error is returned\n233: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n234:   1. Increment the retry counter for the resource\n235:   2. Calculate backoff delay using exponential backoff (base 5ms, max 1000s)\n236:   3. Re-add the request to the queue with the calculated delay\n237:   4. Not block other reconciliations\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Max retries exceeded\n240: - **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation 5 times\n241: - **WHEN** the max retry limit is reached\n242: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n243:   1. Drop the request from the queue\n244:   2. Update the resource status with `Failed` condition\n245:   3. Record the permanent failure in status\n246:   4. Log the error for operator investigation\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Successful reconciliation resets rate limit\n249: - **GIVEN** a resource that previously failed reconciliation\n250: - **WHEN** the reconciliation succeeds\n251: - **THEN** the system SHALL reset the retry counter for that resource to zero\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Concurrent workers process queue\n254: - **GIVEN** the controller is configured with 3 concurrent workers\n255: - **WHEN** multiple requests are in the queue\n256: - **THEN** the system SHALL process up to 3 reconciliations concurrently\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: Exponential Backoff for Failures\n261: \n262: The system SHALL implement exponential backoff for transient failures.\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Calculate backoff delay\n265: - **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation `n` times\n266: - **WHEN** calculating the next retry delay\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the formula: `min(base * 2^n, max)` where base=5ms, max=1000s\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Apply jitter to backoff\n270: - **GIVEN** a calculated backoff of 10 seconds\n271: - **WHEN** scheduling the retry\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL add ┬▒10% jitter to prevent thundering herd\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: Reset backoff on success\n275: - **GIVEN** a resource with accumulated backoff delay\n276: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n277: - **THEN** the system SHALL reset the backoff to the base value\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Skip backoff for non-retryable errors\n280: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a non-retryable error (e.g., invalid spec)\n281: - **WHEN** the error is returned\n282: - **THEN** the system SHALL not retry and update status with permanent failure\n283: \n284: ---\n285: \n286: ### Requirement: Finalizer Handling\n287: \n288: The system SHALL implement finalizers for graceful resource cleanup.\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n291: - **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime resource without finalizers\n292: - **WHEN** the reconciler first processes the resource\n293: - **THEN** it SHALL add the finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Execute finalizer on deletion\n296: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n297: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n298: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n299:   1. Check if deletion timestamp is set\n300:   2. Execute cleanup logic (delete pods, services)\n301:   3. Remove the finalizer from the resource\n302:   4. Return to allow Kubernetes deletion\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Multiple finalizers handling\n305: - **GIVEN** a resource with multiple finalizers including the controller's finalizer\n306: - **WHEN** processing deletion\n307: - **THEN** the system SHALL only remove its own finalizer and preserve others\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Finalizer cleanup failure\n310: - **GIVEN** cleanup fails during finalizer execution (e.g., API server error)\n311: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n312: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n313:   1. Not remove the finalizer\n314:   2. Return the error to trigger retry\n315:   3. Keep the resource in terminating state\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter finalizer\n318: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter resource\n319: - **WHEN** processed by the reconciler\n320: - **THEN** it SHALL use finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ### Requirement: Status Updates and Condition Management\n325: \n326: The system SHALL properly manage resource status and conditions.\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n329: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime reconciliation determines new state\n330: - **WHEN** updating status\n331: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n332:   1. Use the status subresource update (`UpdateStatus`)\n333:   2. Set appropriate phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n334:   3. Update conditions with proper transition timestamps\n335:   4. Preserve existing conditions not being modified\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Add new condition\n338: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime without a `SandboxCreated` condition\n339: - **WHEN** the sandbox is created\n340: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n341:   1. Append a new `AgentRuntimeCondition` to the conditions array\n342:   2. Set `Type`, `Status`, `LastTransitionTime`, `Reason`, and `Message`\n343:   3. Use strategic merge patch to avoid conflicts\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Update existing condition\n346: - **GIVEN** an existing condition with status `False`\n347: - **WHEN** the condition status changes to `True`\n348: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n349:   1. Update the `Status` field\n350:   2. Update `LastTransitionTime` to now\n351:   3. Update `Reason` and `Message` if provided\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Observed generation tracking\n354: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `metadata.generation=5`\n355: - **WHEN** spec reconciliation completes\n356: - **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.observedGeneration=5`\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Handle status update conflict\n359: - **GIVEN** a status update fails with conflict error\n360: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n361: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n362:   1. Fetch the latest resource version\n363:   2. Re-apply the status changes\n364:   3. Retry the update (up to 3 times)\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter ready status\n367: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with running sandbox\n368: - **WHEN** all readiness checks pass\n369: - **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.ready=true` and update conditions\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ### Requirement: OwnerReference Management\n374: \n375: The system SHALL set OwnerReferences on created resources for garbage collection.\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Pod\n378: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime creates a sandbox Pod\n379: - **WHEN** creating the Pod\n380: - **THEN** the system SHALL set:\n381:   ```yaml\n382:   ownerReferences:\n383:   - apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n384:     kind: AgentRuntime\n385:     name: <agentruntime-name>\n386:     uid: <agentruntime-uid>\n387:     controller: true\n388:     blockOwnerDeletion: true\n389:   ```\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Service\n392: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a Service\n393: - **WHEN** creating the Service\n394: - **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference pointing to the CodeInterpreter\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on ConfigMap\n397: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a ConfigMap for configuration\n398: - **WHEN** creating the ConfigMap\n399: - **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference for automatic cleanup\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Cascade deletion with OwnerReference\n402: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with OwnerReference-set Pods\n403: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is deleted\n404: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL automatically garbage collect the owned Pods\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ### Requirement: Integration with WorkloadManager Service Layer\n409: \n410: The system SHALL integrate with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP service.\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: Reconciler updates Store via service layer\n413: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation updates sandbox status\n414: - **WHEN** status changes from `Pending` to `Running`\n415: - **THEN** the system SHALL call the service layer to update the Store entry\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Service layer triggers reconciliation\n418: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request modifies an AgentRuntime\n419: - **WHEN** the modification is applied via Kubernetes API\n420: - **THEN** the watch SHALL trigger reconciliation\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: Reconciler reads from informer cache\n423: - **GIVEN** the reconciler needs to list related resources\n424: - **WHEN** querying resources\n425: - **THEN** it SHALL use the informer cache for efficiency, falling back to API server on cache miss\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: Shared informer factory\n428: - **GIVEN** both reconcilers and HTTP handlers need resource information\n429: - **WHEN** initializing the system\n430: - **THEN** the system SHALL use a shared informer factory to avoid duplicate watches\n431: \n432: ---\n433: \n434: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n435: \n436: The system SHALL expose metrics for reconciliation operations.\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Expose reconcile latency metric\n439: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation completes\n440: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n441: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_latency_seconds` histogram with labels:\n442:   - `controller` (agentruntime/codeinterpreter)\n443:   - `result` (success/error)\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Expose reconcile count metric\n446: - **GIVEN** reconciliations are being processed\n447: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n448: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_total` counter with labels:\n449:   - `controller`\n450:   - `result`\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Expose queue depth metric\n453: - **GIVEN** the work queue has pending items\n454: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n455: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_queue_depth` gauge per controller\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: Expose retry count metric\n458: - **GIVEN** resources are being retried\n459: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n460: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_retries_total` counter\n461: \n462: #### Scenario: Structured logging for reconciliation\n463: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation is processed\n464: - **WHEN** logging\n465: - **THEN** the system SHALL include fields:\n466:   - `controller`\n467:   - `resource_name`\n468:   - `resource_namespace`\n469:   - `operation` (create/update/delete)\n470:   - `duration_ms`\n471:   - `result`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Log reconciliation errors\n474: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails\n475: - **WHEN** logging the error\n476: - **THEN** the system SHALL include:\n477:   - Error message\n478:   - Stack trace (if available)\n479:   - Resource details\n480:   - Retry count\n481: \n482: ---\n483: \n484: ### Requirement: Error Handling and Recovery\n485: \n486: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully and recover when possible.\n487: \n488: #### Scenario: Handle API server unavailable\n489: - **GIVEN** the Kubernetes API server is temporarily unavailable\n490: - **WHEN** the reconciler tries to fetch/update a resource\n491: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n492:   1. Log the error\n493:   2. Return a retryable error\n494:   3. Requeue with exponential backoff\n495: \n496: #### Scenario: Handle network timeout\n497: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call times out\n498: - **WHEN** the timeout occurs\n499: - **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as retryable and requeue\n500: \n501: #### Scenario: Handle RBAC permission denied\n502: - **GIVEN** the controller lacks permissions for an operation\n503: - **WHEN** a forbidden error occurs\n504: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n505:   1. Log the error with details\n506:   2. Not retry (non-retryable)\n507:   3. Update resource status with failure\n508: \n509: #### Scenario: Handle invalid resource spec\n510: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has an invalid spec\n511: - **WHEN** reconciliation fails validation\n512: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n513:   1. Update status with `Failed` condition\n514:   2. Record validation error in status\n515:   3. Not retry\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: Recover from panic\n518: - **GIVEN** a reconciler panics during execution\n519: - **WHEN** the panic occurs\n520: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n521:   1. Recover from the panic\n522:   2. Log the panic with stack trace\n523:   3. Update metrics\n524:   4. Continue processing other resources\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ### Requirement: Leader Election (Preparation)\n529: \n530: The system SHALL prepare for leader election to support HA deployments.\n531: \n532: #### Scenario: Configure leader election options\n533: - **GIVEN** the controller manager initializes\n534: - **WHEN** setting up the manager\n535: - **THEN** it SHALL accept leader election configuration (disabled by default in this AR)\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: Skip leader election in single-replica mode\n538: - **GIVEN** leader election is not enabled\n539: - **WHEN** the controller starts\n540: - **THEN** it SHALL start immediately without acquiring a lease\n541: \n542: #### Scenario: Leader election resource naming\n543: - **GIVEN** leader election is configured\n544: - **WHEN** acquiring the lease\n545: - **THEN** it SHALL use the lease name `agentcube-workload-manager-leader-election`\n546: \n547: ---\n548: \n549: ## File Index\n550: \n551: | Path | Purpose |\n552: |------|---------|\n553: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/manager.go` | Controller manager bootstrap and lifecycle |\n554: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller.go` | AgentRuntimeReconciler implementation |\n555: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller.go` | CodeInterpreterReconciler implementation |\n556: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | Base reconciler interface and utilities |\n557: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | Finalizer helper functions |\n558: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/conditions.go` | Condition management utilities |\n559: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ownerref.go` | OwnerReference helper functions |\n560: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | Prometheus metrics definitions |\n561: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/watch.go` | Watch event handlers and mappers |\n562: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ratelimiter.go` | Rate limiter configuration |\n563: | `cmd/workload-manager/controller.go` | Controller command entry point |\n564: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller_test.go` | AgentRuntime reconciler tests |\n565: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller_test.go` | CodeInterpreter reconciler tests |\n566: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/suite_test.go` | Controller test suite setup |\n567: \n568: ---\n569: \n570: ## Dependencies\n571: \n572: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n573: |------------|---------|---------|\n574: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.20.0+` | Controller runtime framework |\n575: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated clientset and informers |\n576: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes client |\n577: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n578: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics |\n579: | `github.com/go-logr/logr` | Latest | Structured logging |\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## API Integration\n584: \n585: | Component | Usage |\n586: |-----------|-------|\n587: | `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` | Resource type being reconciled |\n588: | `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` | Resource type being reconciled |\n589: | `client-go/informers` | Watch resource changes |\n590: | `client-go/listers` | Cached resource reads |\n591: | `controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Controller-runtime client |\n592: | `controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile` | Reconcile interface |\n593: | `controller-runtime/pkg/controller` | Controller builder |\n594: | `controller-runtime/pkg/manager` | Manager interface |\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Data Types\n599: \n600: ### Reconciler Configuration\n601: ```go\n602: type ReconcilerConfig struct {\n603:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int           // default: 3\n604:     RateLimiterBaseDelay    time.Duration // default: 5ms\n605:     RateLimiterMaxDelay     time.Duration // default: 1000s\n606:     MaxRetries              int           // default: 5\n607:     GracefulShutdownTimeout time.Duration // default: 30s\n608: }\n609: ```\n610: \n611: ### Reconcile Result\n612: ```go\n613: type ReconcileResult struct {\n614:     Requeue      bool\n615:     RequeueAfter time.Duration\n616:     Error        error\n617: }\n618: ```\n619: \n620: ### Finalizer Constants\n621: ```go\n622: const (\n623:     AgentRuntimeFinalizer    = \"agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n624:     CodeInterpreterFinalizer = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n625: )\n626: ```\n627: \n628: ---\n629: \n630: ## Metrics Reference\n631: \n632: | Metric Name | Type | Labels | Description |\n633: |-------------|------|--------|-------------|\n634: | `reconcile_latency_seconds` | Histogram | controller, result | Reconciliation duration |\n635: | `reconcile_total` | Counter | controller, result | Total reconciliations |\n636: | `reconcile_queue_depth` | Gauge | controller | Current queue depth |\n637: | `reconcile_retries_total` | Counter | controller | Total retries |\n638: | `resource_status_phase` | Gauge | controller, phase | Resources by phase |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Notes\n643: \n644: - The reconciler uses controller-runtime for efficient resource watching and reconciliation\n645: - Rate limiting prevents thundering herd on API server errors\n646: - Finalizers ensure cleanup before resource deletion\n647: - OwnerReferences enable Kubernetes garbage collection\n648: - Status updates use the subresource to avoid spec conflicts\n649: - The controller integrates with existing WorkloadManager HTTP service\n650: - Metrics are exposed via the same `/metrics` endpoint as the HTTP service\n651: - Leader election is prepared but not required for single-replica deployments\n652: - All controllers share a single manager and informer cache for efficiency\n\n(End of file - total 652 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ©\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n\n#### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775852050546,"end":1775852050587}}}}
