{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852056945,"sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","part":{"id":"prt_d7907ecce00141uxSUmgasoUdW","messageID":"msg_d7907d8cd001s2CV20VWDT0zEB","sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 Tasks: Sandbox ÕłøÕ╗║ÕżäńÉåÕÖ© (Sandbox Creation Processor)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** M  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Task 1: Create Core Data Types\n11: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/types/request.go` and `pkg/workloadmanager/types/response.go` updated with sandbox types\n12: \n13: - [ ] Add `CreateSandboxRequest` struct with fields: Kind, Name, Namespace\n14: - [ ] Implement `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` method\n15:   - Verify test: returns error when Kind is empty or invalid\n16:   - Verify test: returns error when Name is empty\n17:   - Verify test: returns error when Namespace is empty\n18:   - Verify test: returns nil for valid request\n19: - [ ] Add `CreateSandboxResponse` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints\n20: - [ ] Add `SandboxEntryPoint` struct with fields: Path, Protocol, Endpoint\n21: - [ ] Add `SandboxInfo` struct for Store persistence\n22: - [ ] Verify all structs have proper JSON tags (camelCase)\n23: \n24: **Verification Command:**\n25: ```bash\n26: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/types/... -v -run \"TestCreateSandboxRequest\"\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Task 2: Implement Workload Builder - Sandbox Object Construction\n32: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `buildSandboxObject()` function\n33: \n34: - [ ] Create `workload_builder.go` file\n35: - [ ] Implement `buildSandboxObject(runtime *AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n36:   - Generate sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n37:   - Set APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n38:   - Set Kind: `Sandbox`\n39:   - Add required labels (session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by)\n40:   - Add annotations (idle-timeout)\n41:   - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n42:   - Set replicas to 1\n43:   - Set lifecycle.shutdownTime\n44: - [ ] Write unit tests in `workload_builder_test.go`\n45:   - Verify test: sandbox name format is correct\n46:   - Verify test: all required labels are present\n47:   - Verify test: podTemplate is correctly copied\n48:   - Verify test: returns error when Template is nil\n49: \n50: **Verification Command:**\n51: ```bash\n52: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildSandboxObject\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Task 3: Implement Workload Builder - SandboxClaim Object Construction\n58: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `buildSandboxClaimObject()` function\n59: \n60: - [ ] Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject(runtime *CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n61:   - Set APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n62:   - Set Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n63:   - Generate claim name with 8-char random suffix\n64:   - Add minimal metadata (session-id, workload-name labels)\n65: - [ ] Write unit tests in `workload_builder_test.go`\n66:   - Verify test: SandboxClaim has correct APIVersion and Kind\n67:   - Verify test: name follows expected format\n68: \n69: **Verification Command:**\n70: ```bash\n71: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildSandboxClaimObject\"\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## Task 4: Implement Workload Builder - CodeInterpreter Sandbox Construction\n