{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852438523,"sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","part":{"id":"prt_d7908767c001kC6Hpfe3Qno9zx","messageID":"msg_d7907f1a90013l55haURwJVApX","sessionID":"ses_286f86a25ffeF7KWMlK4TQYGRC","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","content":"# AR-007 Tasks: K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ©\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** L  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Create Controller Directory Structure\n**Verifiable Output:** Directory structure created for controller package\n\n- [ ] Create directory `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`\n- [ ] Create directory `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/internal/`\n- [ ] Verify directory structure exists\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\nls -la pkg/workloadmanager/controller/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Create Reconciler Configuration Types\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/config.go` with ReconcilerConfig struct\n\n- [ ] Create `config.go` file\n- [ ] Define `ReconcilerConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `MaxConcurrentReconciles int` (default: 3)\n  - `RateLimiterBaseDelay time.Duration` (default: 5ms)\n  - `RateLimiterMaxDelay time.Duration` (default: 1000s)\n  - `MaxRetries int` (default: 5)\n  - `GracefulShutdownTimeout time.Duration` (default: 30s)\n- [ ] Add `DefaultReconcilerConfig()` function returning defaults\n- [ ] Add validation method `Validate() error`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: defaults are correct\n  - Verify test: validation catches invalid values (negative, zero)\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestReconcilerConfig\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Create Finalizer Constants and Helpers\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` with finalizer utilities\n\n- [ ] Create `finalizer.go` file\n- [ ] Define constants:\n  - `AgentRuntimeFinalizer = \"agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer\"`\n  - `CodeInterpreterFinalizer = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer\"`\n- [ ] Implement `HasFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n- [ ] Implement `AddFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n  - Returns true if finalizer was added (not already present)\n- [ ] Implement `RemoveFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n  - Returns true if finalizer was removed (was present)\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: HasFinalizer returns true when present\n  - Verify test: HasFinalizer returns false when absent\n  - Verify test: AddFinalizer adds only if not present\n  - Verify test: RemoveFinalizer removes only if present\n  - Verify test: RemoveFinalizer preserves other finalizers\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestFinalizer\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Create OwnerReference Helpers\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ownerref.go` with OwnerReference utilities\n\n- [ ] Create `ownerref.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `NewOwnerReference(owner client.Object, scheme *runtime.Scheme) (*metav1.OwnerReference, error)`\n  - Sets `Controller: true`\n  - Sets `BlockOwnerDeletion: true`\n  - Extracts APIVersion and Kind from scheme\n- [ ] Implement `SetOwnerReference(obj metav1.Object, ownerRef *metav1.OwnerReference)`\n- [ ] Implement `HasOwnerReference(obj metav1.Object, ownerUID types.UID) bool`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: OwnerReference has correct fields\n  - Verify test: Controller and BlockOwnerDeletion are true\n  - Verify test: HasOwnerReference finds by UID\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestOwnerReference\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Create Condition Management Utilities\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/conditions.go` with condition helpers\n\n- [ ] Create `conditions.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `SetCondition(conditions *[]runtimev1alpha1.Condition, condition runtimev1alpha1.Condition) bool`\n  - Updates existing condition if type matches\n  - Appends new condition if type doesn't exist\n  - Updates LastTransitionTime only when status changes\n  - Returns true if condition was modified\n- [ ] Implement `GetCondition(conditions []runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) *runtimev1alpha1.Condition`\n- [ ] Implement `RemoveCondition(conditions *[]runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) bool`\n- [ ] Implement `IsConditionTrue(conditions []runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) bool`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: SetCondition adds new condition\n  - Verify test: SetCondition updates existing with status change\n  - Verify test: LastTransitionTime updates only on status change\n  - Verify test: GetCondition returns correct condition\n  - Verify test: RemoveCondition removes only specified type\n  - Verify test: IsConditionTrue works correctly\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCondition\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Create Metrics Definitions\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` with Prometheus metrics\n\n- [ ] Create `metrics.go` file\n- [ ] Define metrics:\n  - `reconcileLatency = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(...)` with labels: controller, result\n  - `reconcileTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(...)` with labels: controller, result\n  - `reconcileQueueDepth = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(...)` with label: controller\n  - `reconcileRetriesTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(...)` with label: controller\n- [ ] Implement `RecordReconcileLatency(controller string, duration time.Duration, success bool)`\n- [ ] Implement `RecordReconcile(controller string, success bool)`\n- [ ] Implement `SetQueueDepth(controller string, depth int)`\n- [ ] Implement `RecordRetry(controller string)`\n- [ ] Implement `RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: metrics are registered without error\n  - Verify test: recording metrics doesn't panic\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestMetrics\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: Create Rate Limiter Configuration\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ratelimiter.go` with rate limiter setup\n\n- [ ] Create `ratelimiter.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `NewRateLimiter(baseDelay, maxDelay time.Duration) workqueue.RateLimiter`\n  - Uses `workqueue.NewItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter(baseDelay, maxDelay)`\n- [ ] Implement `NewControllerRateLimiter(config ReconcilerConfig) workqueue.RateLimiter`\n  - Creates rate limiter with config values\n  - Adds ┬▒10% jitter to prevent thundering herd\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: rate limiter is created with correct delays\n  - Verify test: backoff increases exponentially\n  - Verify test: backoff is capped at max delay\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestRateLimiter\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: Create Base Reconciler Interface\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` with base reconciler\n\n- [ ] Create `reconciler.go` file\n- [ ] Define `Reconciler` interface:\n  - `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n- [ ] Define `ReconcileResult` struct (wrapper for controller-runtime result)\n- [ ] Implement `Requeue() ReconcileResult`\n- [ ] Implement `RequeueAfter(duration time.Duration) ReconcileResult`\n- [ ] Implement `Done() ReconcileResult`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: Requeue returns Requeue=true\n  - Verify test: RequeueAfter returns correct duration\n  - Verify test: Done returns empty result\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestReconcileResult\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 9: Create Controller Manager Bootstrap\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/manager.go` with manager setup\n\n- [ ] Create `manager.go` file\n- [ ] Define `ControllerManager` struct with fields:\n  - `mgr ctrl.Manager`\n  - `config ReconcilerConfig`\n  - `started bool`\n- [ ] Implement `NewControllerManager(kubeconfig *rest.Config, config ReconcilerConfig) (*ControllerManager, error)`\n  - Creates controller-runtime manager\n  - Registers scheme with CRD types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n  - Sets up health probe endpoints\n- [ ] Write unit tests with envtest\n  - Verify test: manager is created successfully\n  - Verify test: scheme is registered with CRD types\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestControllerManager\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 10: Create AgentRuntime Reconciler Structure\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller.go` with reconciler struct\n\n- [ ] Create `agentruntime_controller.go` file\n- [ ] Define `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct with fields:\n  - `client client.Client`\n  - `scheme *runtime.Scheme`\n  - `config ReconcilerConfig`\n  - `recorder record.EventRecorder`\n- [ ] Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme, config ReconcilerConfig) *AgentRuntimeReconciler`\n- [ ] Implement `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error`\n  - Uses `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr)`\n  - For type `&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}`\n  - Owns Pods (for status updates)\n  - With event filter (skip status-only updates)\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: reconciler is initialized correctly\n  - Verify test: SetupWithManager configures controller correctly\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcilerSetup\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 11: Implement AgentRuntime Reconcile - Fetch and Initial Setup\n**Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime reconciler fetches resource and handles not found\n\n- [ ] Implement fetch logic in `Reconcile()` method:\n  - Fetch AgentRuntime by namespaced name\n  - Handle NotFound error (return Done, nil - object was deleted)\n- [ ] Implement initial status setup:\n  - If status.phase is empty, set to Pending\n- [ ] Add finalizer if not present\n- [ ] Write unit tests with fake client\n  - Verify test: returns Done when resource not found\n  - Verify test: sets phase to Pending on new resource\n  - Verify test: adds finalizer on first reconcile\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileFetch\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 12: Implement AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation\n**Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime reconciler creates sandbox Pod\n\n- [ ] Implement sandbox creation logic:\n  - Check if sandbox Pod exists (by OwnerReference)\n  - If not exists, create Pod from AgentRuntime spec\n  - Set OwnerReference on created Pod\n  - Add `SandboxCreated` condition\n- [ ] Implement `getOrCreateSandboxPod(ctx, agentRuntime) (*corev1.Pod, error)` helper\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: creates Pod when none exists\n  - Verify test: reuses existing Pod when present\n  - Verify test: Pod has correct OwnerReference\n  - Verify test: SandboxCreated condition is set\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileSandbox\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 13: Implement AgentRuntime Status Updates\n**Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime status reflects sandbox state\n\n- [ ] Implement status update based on Pod state:\n  - Pod Pending ŌåÆ AgentRuntime Pending\n  - Pod Running ŌåÆ AgentRuntime Running (with PodIP, SandboxID, StartTime)\n  - Pod Failed ŌåÆ AgentRuntime Failed\n- [ ] Implement `updateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, pod) error`\n  - Sets phase, conditions, and status fields\n  - Uses `client.Status().Update()`\n- [ ] Handle status update conflicts (retry up to 3 times)\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: phase transitions from Pending to Running\n  - Verify test: PodIP is recorded in status\n  - Verify test: SandboxID (Pod UID) is recorded\n  - Verify test: Ready condition is set when Running\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileStatus\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 14: Implement AgentRuntime Deletion Handling\n**Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime finalizer handles cleanup\n\n- [ ] Implement deletion handling:\n  - Check if DeletionTimestamp is set\n  - If finalizer present, execute cleanup\n  - Delete associated sandbox Pod\n  - Delete associated Services/Ingress if any\n  - Remove finalizer after cleanup\n- [ ] Implement `handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(ctx, agentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: cleanup runs when deletion timestamp set\n  - Verify test: Pod is deleted during cleanup\n  - Verify test: finalizer is removed after cleanup\n  - Verify test: resource deletion proceeds after finalizer removal\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileDeletion\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 15: Implement AgentRuntime Spec Updates\n**Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime handles spec changes\n\n- [ ] Implement spec change detection:\n  - Compare Generation with ObservedGeneration\n  - If different, handle as update\n- [ ] Implement update logic:\n  - Set phase to Pending during update\n  - Apply new spec to sandbox\n  - Update ObservedGeneration after successful reconcile\n- [ ] Implement `handleAgentRuntimeUpdate(ctx, agentRuntime) error`\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: spec change triggers update handling\n  - Verify test: ObservedGeneration is updated after reconcile\n  - Verify test: p